      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "The Muslim Academy of Greater Orlando exhibits a robust growth trajectory, evidenced by its <cite id=\"4\">25.5% revenue CAGR</cite> over the last three years. This growth is supported by a <cite id=\"14\">documented theory of change</cite> that integrates <cite id=\"15\">professional development programs</cite> for staff with <cite id=\"16\">rigorous admission requirements</cite> for students. Its financial health is further underscored by <cite id=\"17\">total assets of $3,270,864</cite> and a lean fundraising model that maximizes the utility of <cite id=\"5\">$3,093,110 in annual contributions</cite>."
      ],
      "summary": "The Muslim Academy of Greater Orlando (MAGO) is a non-profit educational institution that has served the Florida community since its <cite id=\"1\">founding in 2006</cite>. The academy provides a faith-based educational foundation for children from <cite id=\"2\">Pre-K through 8th grade</cite>, focusing on a mission of virtue, wisdom, and strength. In the 2024 tax year, the organization reported <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $3,572,587</cite>, representing a significant <cite id=\"4\">three-year revenue CAGR of 25.5%</cite>. While the school is primarily tuition-funded, it relies on <cite id=\"5\">contributions totaling over $3 million</cite> to sustain its operations and <cite id=\"6\">service learning projects</cite>. The institution is <cite id=\"7\">accredited by Cognia</cite> and has been recognized as being within the <cite id=\"8\">top 20% of private schools in Florida</cite>. Despite its academic success, the organization maintains a <cite id=\"9\">program expense ratio of 67.8%</cite> according to recent filings, though third-party analysis by Charity Navigator suggests a <cite id=\"10\">67.8% program ratio</cite> when accounting for administrative allocations. The academy demonstrates exceptional financial stability, maintaining <cite id=\"11\">15.6 months of working capital reserves</cite> and achieving a <cite id=\"12\">fundraising efficiency of $0.00 spent</cite> to raise every dollar.",
